arChildNodes.szComment:
ERU works his magic on the archway. Light subtly shimmers across the threshold. 

Chant pronunciation:
Roh-yee-seh woo kee-seh, roh-yee-seh woo woot-sah. Wok bee weh seh, wok bahn-gee woo cho-wom. 

 peh woo soh-cha weh-kee pee pah chim ah-heh. Cho peh-nehn chee oh woo, 

Eh bahn.

Maka joins in Eru's chant as she walks to the other side. 

Chant pronunciation:
Roh-yee-seh woo kee-seh, roh-yee-seh woo woot-sah. Wok bee weh seh, wok bahn-gee woo cho-wom. 

 peh woo soh-cha weh-kee pee pah chim ah-heh. Cho peh-nehn chee oh woo, 

Eh bahn.

Maka pulls out an OBSIDIAN DAGGER. The chant reaches a crescendo, Maka and Eru booming the final syllable in unison.
Silence eerily and suddenly falls over the space for a moment. 
Then, with no warning, Maka plunges the blade into the archway’s empty space. 
The Player cringes, arching their back in agony, as if they’ve just been stabbed.
We see a shadowy figure in the archway, its movements mirroring the Player’s. Maka’s dagger is plunged firmly in its back, protruding from its chest.
The Player spasms as they invite the pain in.

With great effort, Maka begins to powerfully and haltingly DRAG the blade down. We hear the sound of flesh being hacked open, bones snapping under her blade. 
The Player’s real body looks unharmed, though they WRITHE in unspeakable agony.
Eru leans over and grips the edges of the figure’s wound. He PULLS. A portal opens within the widening gash.
